# The Pharmacology of Mucormycosis Treatment

Russell E. Lewis,. Pharm.D., FCCP
Associate Professor, Infectious Diseases
Department of Molecular Microbiology
University of Padua, Padua, ITaly

## Abstract

Survival from invasive mucormycosis often depends on the timely administration of effective systemic antifungal agents. 

## Introduction

Invasive mucormycosis is an aggressive and often life-threating fungal infection 

